  },
  {
    question: "What fencing enquiries arrive through Facebook?",
    answer: "The majority are domestic — homeowners who have seen your work on Facebook, been recommended by a friend, or found your page while searching for local fencing companies. Common requests involve boundary panel replacements, close board upgrades, gate installations, and storm damage repairs. Occasionally, smallholding and equestrian clients also enquire through Facebook about post and rail or stock fencing."
  },
  {
    question: "How quickly does the AI respond on Messenger?",
    answer: "Responses arrive within seconds. Facebook Messenger shows read receipts, so the homeowner knows their enquiry has been seen and is being handled. After a storm when homeowners are messaging multiple fencing companies simultaneously, this speed advantage is decisive — the first professional response typically secures the site visit."
